actions.description: Grants permission to delete topics on a cluster, equivalent to Apache Kafka's DELETE TOPIC ACL

actions.description: Grants permission to describe various aspects of the cluster, equivalent to Apache Kafka's DESCRIBE CLUSTER ACL

actions.description: Grants permission to describe the dynamic configuration of a cluster, equivalent to Apache Kafka's DESCRIBE_CONFIGS CLUSTER ACL

actions.description: Grants permission to describe topics on a cluster, equivalent to Apache Kafka's DESCRIBE TOPIC ACL

actions.description: Grants permission to describe the dynamic configuration of topics on a cluster, equivalent to Apache Kafka's DESCRIBE_CONFIGS TOPIC ACL

actions.description: Grants permission to describe transactional IDs on a cluster, equivalent to Apache Kafka's DESCRIBE TRANSACTIONAL_ID ACL

actions.name: ReadData
actions.description: Grants permission to read data from topics on a cluster, equivalent to Apache Kafka's READ TOPIC ACL

actions.name: WriteData
actions.description: Grants permission to write data to topics on a cluster, equivalent to Apache Kafka's WRITE TOPIC ACL

actions.description: Grants permission to write data idempotently on a cluster, equivalent to Apache Kafka's IDEMPOTENT_WRITE CLUSTER ACL

actions.description: Grants permission to BatchDeleteImportData API. BatchDeleteImportData deletes one or more Migration Hub import tasks, each identified by their import ID. Each import task has a number of records, which can identify servers or applications

actions.name: CreateApplication
actions.description: Grants permission to CreateApplication API. CreateApplication creates an application with the given name and description

actions.name: CreateTags
actions.description: Grants permission to CreateTags API. CreateTags creates one or more tags for configuration items. Tags are metadata that help you categorize IT assets. This API accepts a list of multiple configuration items

actions.name: DeleteApplications
actions.description: Grants permission to DeleteApplications API. DeleteApplications deletes a list of applications and their associations with configuration items

actions.name: DeleteTags
actions.description: Grants permission to DeleteTags API. DeleteTags deletes the association between configuration items and one or more tags. This API accepts a list of multiple configuration items

actions.name: DescribeAgents
actions.description: Grants permission to DescribeAgents API. DescribeAgents lists agents or the Connector by ID or lists all agents/Connectors associated with your user if you did not specify an ID

actions.name: DescribeConfigurations
actions.description: Grants permission to DescribeConfigurations API. DescribeConfigurations retrieves attributes for a list of configuration item IDs. All of the supplied IDs must be for the same asset type (server, application, process, or connection). Output fields are specific to the asset type selected. For example, the output for a server configuration item includes a list of attributes about the server, such as host name, operating system, and number of network cards

actions.name: DescribeContinuousExports
actions.description: Grants permission to DescribeContinuousExports API. DescribeContinuousExports lists exports as specified by ID. All continuous exports associated with your user can be listed if you call DescribeContinuousExports as is without passing any parameters

actions.name: DescribeExportConfigurations
actions.description: Grants permission to DescribeExportConfigurations API. DescribeExportConfigurations retrieves the status of a given export process. You can retrieve status from a maximum of 100 processes

actions.name: DescribeExportTasks
actions.description: Grants permission to DescribeExportTasks API. DescribeExportTasks retrieve status of one or more export tasks. You can retrieve the status of up to 100 export tasks

actions.name: DescribeImportTasks
actions.description: Grants permission to DescribeImportTasks API. DescribeImportTasks returns an array of import tasks for your user, including status information, times, IDs, the Amazon S3 Object URL for the import file, and more

actions.name: DescribeTags
actions.description: Grants permission to DescribeTags API. DescribeTags retrieves a list of configuration items that are tagged with a specific tag. Or retrieves a list of all tags assigned to a specific configuration item

actions.name: DisassociateConfigurationItemsFromApplication
actions.description: Grants permission to DisassociateConfigurationItemsFromApplication API. DisassociateConfigurationItemsFromApplication disassociates one or more configuration items from an application

actions.name: ExportConfigurations
actions.description: Grants permission to ExportConfigurations API. ExportConfigurations exports all discovered configuration data to an Amazon S3 bucket or an application that enables you to view and evaluate the data. Data includes tags and tag associations, processes, connections, servers, and system performance

actions.name: GetDiscoverySummary
actions.description: Grants permission to GetDiscoverySummary API. GetDiscoverySummary retrieves a short summary of discovered assets

actions.name: GetNetworkConnectionGraph
actions.description: Grants permission to GetNetworkConnectionGraph API. GetNetworkConnectionGraph accepts input list of one of - Ip Addresses, server ids or node ids. Returns a list of nodes and edges which help customer visualize network connection graph. This API is used for visualize network graph functionality in MigrationHub console

actions.name: ListConfigurations
actions.description: Grants permission to ListConfigurations API. ListConfigurations retrieves a list of configuration items according to criteria you specify in a filter. The filter criteria identify relationship requirements

actions.name: ListServerNeighbors
actions.description: Grants permission to ListServerNeighbors API. ListServerNeighbors retrieves a list of servers which are one network hop away from a specified server

actions.name: StartContinuousExport
actions.description: Grants permission to StartContinuousExport API. StartContinuousExport start the continuous flow of agent's discovered data into Amazon Athena

actions.name: StartDataCollectionByAgentIds
actions.description: Grants permission to StartDataCollectionByAgentIds API. StartDataCollectionByAgentIds instructs the specified agents or Connectors to start collecting data

actions.name: StartExportTask
actions.description: Grants permission to StartExportTask API. StartExportTask export the configuration data about discovered configuration items and relationships to an S3 bucket in a specified format

actions.name: StartImportTask
actions.description: Grants permission to StartImportTask API. StartImportTask starts an import task. The Migration Hub import feature allows you to import details of your on-premises environment directly into AWS without having to use the Application Discovery Service (ADS) tools such as the Discovery Connector or Discovery Agent. This gives you the option to perform migration assessment and planning directly from your imported data including the ability to group your devices as applications and track their migration status

actions.name: CreateAppBlock
actions.description: Grants permission to create an app block. App blocks store details about the virtual hard disk that contains the files for the application in an S3 bucket. It also stores the setup script with details about how to mount the virtual hard disk. App blocks are only supported for Elastic fleets

actions.name: CreateAppBlockBuilder
actions.description: Grants permission to create an app block builder. An app block builder is a virtual machine that is used to create an app block

actions.name: CreateAppBlockBuilderStreamingURL
actions.description: Grants permission to create a URL to start an app block builder streaming session

actions.name: CreateApplication
actions.description: Grants permission to create an application within customer account. Applications store the details about how to launch applications on streaming instances. This is only supported for Elastic fleets

actions.name: CreateDirectoryConfig
actions.description: Grants permission to create a Directory Config object in AppStream 2.0. This object includes the configuration information required to join fleets and image builders to Microsoft Active Directory domains

actions.name: CreateEntitlement
actions.description: Grants permission to create an entitlement to control access to applications based on user attributes

actions.name: CreateFleet
actions.description: Grants permission to create a fleet. A fleet is a group of streaming instances from which applications are launched and streamed to users

actions.name: CreateImageBuilder
actions.description: Grants permission to create an image builder. An image builder is a virtual machine that is used to create an image

actions.name: CreateImageBuilderStreamingURL
actions.description: Grants permission to create a URL to start an image builder streaming session

actions.name: CreateStack
actions.description: Grants permission to create a stack to start streaming applications to users. A stack consists of an associated fleet, user access policies, and storage configurations

actions.name: CreateStreamingURL
actions.description: Grants permission to create a temporary URL to start an AppStream 2.0 streaming session for the specified user. A streaming URL enables application streaming to be tested without user setup

actions.name: CreateUpdatedImage
actions.description: Grants permission to update an existing image within customer account

actions.name: CreateUsageReportSubscription
actions.description: Grants permission to create a usage report subscription. Usage reports are generated daily

actions.name: CreateUser
actions.description: Grants permission to create a new user in the user pool

actions.name: DeleteAppBlock
actions.description: Grants permission to delete the specified app block

actions.name: DeleteAppBlockBuilder
actions.description: Grants permission to delete the specified app block builder and release capacity

actions.name: DeleteApplication
actions.description: Grants permission to delete the specified application

actions.name: DeleteDirectoryConfig
actions.description: Grants permission to delete the specified Directory Config object from AppStream 2.0. This object includes the configuration information required to join fleets and image builders to Microsoft Active Directory domains

actions.name: DeleteEntitlement
actions.description: Grants permission to delete the specified entitlement

actions.name: DeleteFleet
actions.description: Grants permission to delete the specified fleet

actions.name: DeleteImage
actions.description: Grants permission to delete the specified image. An image cannot be deleted when it is in use

actions.name: DeleteImageBuilder
actions.description: Grants permission to delete the specified image builder and release capacity

actions.name: DeleteImagePermissions
actions.description: Grants permission to delete permissions for the specified private image

actions.name: DeleteStack
actions.description: Grants permission to delete the specified stack. After the stack is deleted, the application streaming environment provided by the stack is no longer available to users. Also, any reservations made for application streaming sessions for the stack are released

actions.name: DeleteUsageReportSubscription
actions.description: Grants permission to disable usage report generation

actions.name: DeleteUser
actions.description: Grants permission to delete a user from the user pool

actions.name: GetDetectors
actions.description: Grants permission to get all detectors or a single detector if a detectorId is specified. This is a paginated API. If you provide a null maxResults, this action retrieves a maximum of 10 records per page. If you provide a maxResults, the value must be between 5 and 10. To get the next page results, provide the pagination token from the GetDetectorsResponse as part of your request. A null pagination token fetches the records from the beginning

actions.name: GetEntityTypes
actions.description: Grants permission to get all entity types or a specific entity type if a name is specified. This is a paginated API. If you provide a null maxResults, this action retrieves a maximum of 10 records per page. If you provide a maxResults, the value must be between 5 and 10. To get the next page results, provide the pagination token from the GetEntityTypesResponse as part of your request. A null pagination token fetches the records from the beginning

actions.name: GetEvent
actions.description: Grants permission to get the details of the specified event

actions.name: GetEventPrediction
actions.description: Grants permission to evaluate an event against a detector version. If a version ID is not provided, the detector’s (ACTIVE) version is used

actions.name: GetEventPredictionMetadata
actions.description: Grants permission to get more details of a particular prediction

actions.name: GetEventTypes
actions.description: Grants permission to get all event types or a specific event type if name is provided. This is a paginated API. If you provide a null maxResults, this action retrieves a maximum of 10 records per page. If you provide a maxResults, the value must be between 5 and 10. To get the next page results, provide the pagination token from the GetEventTypesResponse as part of your request. A null pagination token fetches the records from the beginning

actions.name: GetExternalModels
actions.description: Grants permission to get the details for one or more Amazon SageMaker models that have been imported into the service. This is a paginated API. If you provide a null maxResults, this actions retrieves a maximum of 10 records per page. If you provide a maxResults, the value must be between 5 and 10. To get the next page results, provide the pagination token from the GetExternalModelsResult as part of your request. A null pagination token fetches the records from the beginning

actions.name: GetKMSEncryptionKey
actions.description: Grants permission to get the encryption key if a Key Management Service (KMS) customer master key (CMK) has been specified to be used to encrypt content in Amazon Fraud Detector

actions.name: GetLabels
actions.description: Grants permission to get all labels or a specific label if name is provided. This is a paginated API. If you provide a null maxResults, this action retrieves a maximum of 50 records per page. If you provide a maxResults, the value must be between 10 and 50. To get the next page results, provide the pagination token from the GetGetLabelsResponse as part of your request. A null pagination token fetches the records from the beginning

actions.name: GetListElements
actions.description: Grants permission to get elements of a list

actions.name: GetListsMetadata
actions.description: Grants permission to get metadata about lists

actions.name: GetModelVersion
actions.description: Grants permission to get the details of the specified model version

actions.name: GetModels
actions.description: Grants permission to get one or more models. Gets all models for the AWS account if no model type and no model id provided. Gets all models for the AWS account and model type, if the model type is specified but model id is not provided. Gets a specific model if (model type, model id) tuple is specified

actions.name: GetOutcomes
actions.description: Grants permission to get one or more outcomes. This is a paginated API. If you provide a null maxResults, this actions retrieves a maximum of 100 records per page. If you provide a maxResults, the value must be between 50 and 100. To get the next page results, provide the pagination token from the GetOutcomesResult as part of your request. A null pagination token fetches the records from the beginning

actions.name: GetRules
actions.description: Grants permission to get all rules for a detector (paginated) if ruleId and ruleVersion are not specified. Gets all rules for the detector and the ruleId if present (paginated). Gets a specific rule if both the ruleId and the ruleVersion are specified

actions.name: GetVariables
actions.description: Grants permission to get all of the variables or the specific variable. This is a paginated API. Providing null maxSizePerPage results in retrieving maximum of 100 records per page. If you provide maxSizePerPage the value must be between 50 and 100. To get the next page result, a provide a pagination token from GetVariablesResult as part of your request. Null pagination token fetches the records from the beginning

actions.name: ListEventPredictions
actions.description: Grants permission to get a list of past predictions

actions.name: ListTagsForResource
actions.description: Grants permission to list all tags associated with the resource. This is a paginated API. To get the next page results, provide the pagination token from the response as part of your request. A null pagination token fetches the records from the beginning

actions.name: PutDetector
actions.description: Grants permission to create or update a detector

actions.name: PutEntityType
actions.description: Grants permission to create or update an entity type. An entity represents who is performing the event. As part of a fraud prediction, you pass the entity ID to indicate the specific entity who performed the event. An entity type classifies the entity. Example classifications include customer, merchant, or account

actions.name: PutEventType
actions.description: Grants permission to create or update an event type. An event is a business activity that is evaluated for fraud risk. With Amazon Fraud Detector, you generate fraud predictions for events. An event type defines the structure for an event sent to Amazon Fraud Detector. This includes the variables sent as part of the event, the entity performing the event (such as a customer), and the labels that classify the event. Example event types include online payment transactions, account registrations, and authentications

actions.name: PutExternalModel
actions.description: Grants permission to create or update an Amazon SageMaker model endpoint. You can also use this action to update the configuration of the model endpoint, including the IAM role and/or the mapped variables

actions.name: PutKMSEncryptionKey

actions.name: PutLabel
actions.description: Grants permission to create or update label. A label classifies an event as fraudulent or legitimate. Labels are associated with event types and used to train supervised machine learning models in Amazon Fraud Detector

actions.name: PutOutcome

actions.name: UpdateDetectorVersion

actions.name: UpdateDetectorVersionMetadata
actions.description: Grants permission to update the detector version's description. You can update the metadata for any detector version (DRAFT, ACTIVE, or INACTIVE)

actions.name: UpdateDetectorVersionStatus
actions.description: Grants permission to update the detector version’s status. You can perform the following promotions or demotions using UpdateDetectorVersionStatus: DRAFT to ACTIVE, ACTIVE to INACTIVE, and INACTIVE to ACTIVE

actions.name: UpdateEventLabel

actions.name: UpdateList

actions.name: UpdateModel
actions.description: Grants permission to update a model. You can update the description attribute using this action

actions.name: UpdateModelVersion
actions.description: Grants permission to update a model version. Updating a model version retrains an existing model version using updated training data and produces a new minor version of the model. You can update the training data set location and data access role attributes using this action. This action creates and trains a new minor version of the model, for example version 1.01, 1.02, 1.03

actions.name: UpdateModelVersionStatus

actions.name: UpdateRuleVersion
actions.description: Grants permission to update a rule version resulting in a new rule version. Updates a rule version resulting in a new rule version (version 1, 2, 3 ...)

conditionKeys.name: kms:KeyOrigin

conditionKeys.name: kms:KeySpec
conditionKeys.description: Filters access to an API operation based on the KeySpec property of the AWS KMS key that is created by or used in the operation. Use it to qualify authorization of the CreateKey operation or any operation that is authorized for a KMS key resource

conditionKeys.name: kms:KeyUsage
conditionKeys.description: Filters access to an API operation based on the KeyUsage property of the AWS KMS key created by or used in the operation. Use it to qualify authorization of the CreateKey operation or any operation that is authorized for a KMS key resource

conditionKeys.name: kms:MultiRegion

conditionKeys.name: kms:MultiRegionKeyType
conditionKeys.description: Filters access to an API operation based on the MultiRegionKeyType property of the AWS KMS key created by or used in the operation. Use it to qualify authorization of the CreateKey operation or any operation that is authorized for a KMS key resource

actions.name: BatchGetTraceSummaryById
actions.description: Grants permission to retrieve metadata for a list of traces specified by ID

actions.name: GetTraceSummaries
actions.description: Grants permission to retrieve IDs and metadata for traces available for a specified time frame using an optional filter. To get the full traces, pass the trace IDs to BatchGetTraces
